<p>A re-imagination of <a href="/scp-699">SCP-699</a>.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Things&nbsp;to&nbsp;think&nbsp;about:</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<ul>
<li>Why, a thousand years in the future, do things like English as we understand it, Minnesota and Wisconsin, paperwork, and the metric system still exist?</li>
<li>The mystery box works differently in this setting than in it does in <a href="/scp-699">SCP-699</a>. Why?</li>
<li>The report attached to the mystery box is changed from the original article. What do the differences imply?</li>
<li>Someone who was probably not under the mystery box's influence at the time wrote that note. What is the appeal of the mystery box?</li>
<li>In a related question, what could have happened in 2597 that is a analogous to a door closing, with the mystery box being a window?</li>
<li>How cool is that logo though? I spent hours getting it right.</li>
</ul>
